cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the task of depth map super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) as it involves generating high-resolution depth maps from low-resolution inputs. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmarking datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
